article.description: Khadeen Harrington scored 14 points and Seton Hall crushed poor-shooting St. Peter's 72-46 on Sunday.
article.headline: Seton Hall cruises against St. Peter's 72-46
article.linkText: Seton Hall cruises against St. Peter's 72-46
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. -- Khadeen Harrington scored 14 points and Seton Hall crushed poor-shooting St. Peter's 72-46 on Sunday. Harrington was 5 of 8 from the floor with four 3-pointers. Seton Hall (8-2) shot 50 percent overall and was 10 of 19 on 3-point attempts. Isaiah Whitehead had 12 points while Angel Delgado scored 10 points and grabbed 10 rebounds. St. Peter's (3-5) shot just 32.7 percent and was 3 of 16 from beyond the arc. Elias Desport was leading scorer for the Peacocks with nine points. Seton Hall raced to a 19-4 lead -- including a pair of 3-pointers by Desi Rodriguez -- and never trailed. A 13-point run later in the first half helped the Pirates forge a 35-20 lead at the break. The lead reached 20 on Whitehead's 3-pointer 56 seconds into the second half and Seton Hall cruised to an easy victory.
